Ingest

age, gender, year, and population

#Load
url_root <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/UN-AVT/kamino-source/main/sources/0-shared/data/"
url_file <- "older-versus-younger/IHME_GBD_2017_POP.csv"
url <- paste0(url_root, url_file)

df <- read.csv(url, header = TRUE)
df

Wrangle

Remove duplicates using filter() and unique()

# Filtering the records
age_levels <- c(
     "Under 5",
     "5 to 9",
     "10 to 14",
     "15 to 19",
     "20 to 24",
     "25 to 29",
     "30 to 34",
     "35 to 39",
     "40 to 44",
     "45 to 49",
     "50 to 54",
     "55 to 59",
     "60 to 64",
     "65 to 69",
     "70 to 74",
     "75 to 79",
     "80 to 84",
     "85 to 89",
     "90 to 94",
     "95 plus")


# Select and filter rows
df_wrangle  <- df[,c(2,4,6,7,11)]%>% 
   filter(str_detect(location_name, 'SDI'))%>%
   filter(sex_name!="Both")%>%
   filter(age_group_name %in% age_levels) %>% 
   filter(year_id == 2017)

# Remove duplicate records
df_wrangle <- unique(df_wrangle)
df_wrangle
